<br />
It's difficult to summarize but the main one I am curious about is that one of the parents has gone all out NSA on their child and promoting that to other parents (in their weird parent meetup group that's not exactly a social event nor required event) do the same. Is that a common parent thing to do nowadays? <br />
<br />
The parent in question monitors all of the child's electronic communications, actively bugs the child's bedroom and computing and communications equipment, and directly interferes with communications (deleting texts received from peers, deleting facebook messages). <br />
<br />
And the parent has the same ideas about pop culture that existed in the past except with pen and paper games instead of MMORPGs.<br />
