It had not occurred to me that kids already enrolled in college nowadays have no first hand memory of 9/11 happening and simply presume the security theater escalation and high level misdirection is the way it has always been until I was watching the movie and the kids in the classroom are given learn about 9/11 as a school assignment. <br />
<br />
That's such a keystone event in modern history on par with the 1948 Arab-Israeli War that I have no idea how kids nowadays can make any sense of things based on the context that they have gathered in upwards of 20 or so years. <br />
<br />
It has to be immensely absurd without that experience. What is more chilling to me though is that having grown up in an environment where things were always this way they most likely will never consider that it can be any other way.</div>

